    "closing": "Interviewing is where hiring decisions actually get made, and it deserves the same structure you'd expect anywhere else in the process. Aster gives candidates control over their own schedule, gives interviewers a real starting point instead of a blank page, and gives hiring managers one team score built from consistent, comparable scorecards instead of scattered opinions. Panels assemble themselves the moment you add someone, reminders go out where candidates actually read them, and every question, score, and decision lives on the candidate's profile for as long as you need it. The team that interviews with structure ends up with a shortlist it can trust, and a candidate experience that doesn't lose good people to a slow, disorganized process."
