        "body": "Slow hiring rarely fails all at once. It fails one stuck stage at a time: a shortlist that sits for a week before anyone reviews it, an interview that takes ten days to get on the calendar, an offer that waits on a signature nobody chased. Aster tracks how long candidates actually sit in each stage, on average and at the extremes, and surfaces the stage where time is piling up fastest. That means you are not scrolling a kanban board trying to eyeball which cards look old. The bottleneck is named, with the numbers to back it up, so \"why is this role slow\" turns into a specific fix: turn on interview self-scheduling if booking is the delay, redistribute scorecards if reviews are stacking up with one person, or check the offer template if signed acceptances are the hold-up. Because this is tracked per role and per stage over time, you can also tell whether a bottleneck is a one-off, caused by a busy week or a single unresponsive manager, or a pattern worth fixing before it costs you candidates who accept somewhere faster."
