        "body": "Every job posting goes out to LinkedIn, JobStreet, the branded career site, referrals, and a sourcing pool you have built up over time, and every one of those channels gets tracked through a source tag on the apply link. Source performance analytics shows which channels bring in applicants who are actually a good match for the role, not just the highest volume. A job board might send fifty applicants and one hire. A referral program might send five and two hires. Without this data, budget goes to whichever channel is loudest or cheapest, not whichever one works. With it, you can retire the job board that never converts, put more weight behind the sourcing pool for hard-to-fill roles, and tell finance exactly why the recruiting budget is allocated the way it is, with numbers instead of instinct. Over a few hiring cycles, this is often the fastest way to cut cost per hire and time-to-hire at once."
