        "title": "Justifying a new recruiter to leadership",
        "body": "You ask for another recruiter every quarter and get the same question back: prove it. Instead of a gut-feel pitch, you pull up the funnel view for the last two quarters, three open roles sitting in interviewing for over three weeks each, heavy drop-off between shortlisted and interviewing, and time-to-hire trending up. The conversation shifts from \"we feel stretched\" to \"here is exactly where capacity is missing and what it is costing us.\" The headcount gets approved."
