        "title": "A new department head, hiring for the first time",
        "body": "A director who's never hired before opens their first req and inherits the same pipeline every other manager uses: the same stages, the same email templates, the same scorecards. You don't have to onboard them onto \"how we hire here\" in a separate meeting, or catch their mistakes after the fact. They see structured, scored candidates from day one, and the audit trail shows you exactly how the first hire went if you ever need to check it."
