        "body": "Scheduling is where founder hiring quietly dies. You mean to reply to a promising candidate, three days pass, and by the time you send three time slots, they've accepted somewhere else. Aster skips that back and forth: once you move someone to interviewing, they get a link to pick a time themselves, and a Google Meet or Microsoft Teams link is created automatically, on your calendar, without you touching a scheduling tool or copying a link into an email. You still decide who gets that link and when, and you can see every booked slot against everything else you have on that day. You just stop being the reason a good candidate went quiet for a week. For a founder juggling product, sales and hiring in the same afternoon, this is the difference between an interview happening this week or not happening at all, and it's often the difference between winning a candidate and losing them to whoever replied first."
