        "body": "Nothing erodes trust with a candidate faster than being contacted twice by the same agency as if they were a stranger both times. Aster's dedup keeps one record per person no matter how many times they apply, which board they come through, or how many briefs they touch. Their full history stays attached: every application, every score, every stage they reached, and every note a recruiter left. That single record carries a rich, shareable candidate profile the whole desk can view with role-based access, plus an audit trail of who did what and when, which matters when several recruiters are working the same pool across different client accounts. Practically, dedup means your talent pool actually gets cleaner and more useful the longer you use it, instead of accumulating duplicate entries that make searches noisy and candidates wonder why nobody at the agency seems to remember them from last time."
